  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized cubes, then add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the potatoes are brown and crispy – these are your <strong>crispy paprika potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1670932680517-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
